<p><b>Maya Deren</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1917-04-29"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="04-29"><a href="/wiki/April_29" title="April 29">April 29</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1917" title="1917">1917</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/Kiev" title="Kiev">Kiev</a> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1961-10-13"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="10-13"><a href="/wiki/October_13" title="October 13">October 13</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1961" title="1961">1961</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/New_York_City" title="New York City">New York City</a>), born <b>Eleanora Derenkowsky</b>, was an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Avant-garde" title="Avant-garde">avant-garde</a> <a href="/wiki/Filmmaker" title="Filmmaker" class="mw-redirect">filmmaker</a> and <a href="/wiki/Film" title="Film">film</a> theorist of the 1940s and 1950s. Deren was also a choreographer, dancer, poet, writer and photographer.</p>
